sub_title: Sustainable development HEMP textile products from Ukraine
summary:
Experienced Owner with a demonstrated history of skills managing her own companies as well as working for international firms. 
Bachelor’s degree in international journalism from Kyiv National Taras Shevchenko University. 

Currently managing own brand of hemp textile and clothing DevoHome

Devohome is a Ukrainian based company that produces healthy and natural hemp textile in Ukraine. 
We grow hemp for production in Poltava region without the use of pesticides. Raw materials are 
processed at our partners plant and the family of the brand owner, Oksana Devoe.
We invented Hemp Fur – plant based fur, a substitute for animal and synthetic 
fur. (https://devohome.com/en/faux_hemp_fur).
Every year we are invited to become part of the global movement for conscious consumption, such as 
Dutch Design Week 2019, 2022, White Milano 2020, Ukranian Fashion Week 2020, MateriaDistrict, and 
many others.
We are official members of Fur Free Retailers and PETA organizations.
In 2019, we received the ELLE Decoration International Design Awards Ukraine 2019 - an international 
award in the field of subject design and interior design for hemp fur.
Furthermore, we are winners of:
“The best sustainable brand in Ukraine by STALO” in 2018
Ukrainian Fashion Industry Award as designer of the year, fur and leather, 2019
“Cruelty-free Fashion 2020” award by UANIMALS.
